content: There will be two different folders in the destination

comment.text: "There will be two different folders in the destination" is a description used to inform users about the expected structure of the target location during folder creation.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Ще има две различни папки в дестинацията' is not the most natural or accurate rendering of 'There will be two different folders in the destination'. 'Дестинацията' (destinatsiyata) is a less common and somewhat formal word for 'destination'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Ще има две различни папки в папката/на местоположението

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'コピー先には2つの異なるフォルダが作成されます' while technically correct, doesn't fully convey the original meaning of 'There will be two different folders in the destination.' It implies the folders are being *created* rather than simply *existing*. A more accurate translation would focus on the existence of the folders.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: コピー先には2つの異なるフォルダが存在します

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation '목표에 두 개의 다른 폴더가 있습니다' translates to 'There are two different folders in the target/goal'. The English phrase 'There will be two different folders in the destination' implies a future action or creation. The Korean translation doesn't convey the sense of 'will be'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: 목표 위치에 두 개의 다른 폴더가 생성될 것입니다.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Lao translation 'ຈະມີໂຟນເດີສອງໂຕແຍກຕ່າງຫາກຢູ່ທີ່ຈຸດຫມາຍປາຍທາງ' translates to 'There will be two different folders separated at the destination.' while the English content 'There will be two different folders in the destination' implies the folders exist *within* the destination, not separated *at* it. The wording suggests a separation *to* the destination.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ຈະມີໂຟນເດີສອງໂຕແຍກຕ່າງຫາກຢູ່ພາຍໃນຈຸດຫມາຍປາຍທາງ

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Două foldere separate vor apărea la destinaţie' is a bit literal. A more natural Romanian phrasing for 'There will be two different folders in the destination' would be something like 'Vor exista două foldere diferite la destinaţie' or 'La destinație vor exista două foldere diferite'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: La destinație vor exista două foldere diferite

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'ගමනාන්තයේ වෙනස් ෆෝල්ඩර දෙකක් ඇත' is not the most natural or accurate translation of 'There will be two different folders in the destination'. ' වෙනස් ' (venas) means 'different', but its use in this context isn't ideal. A more accurate translation would emphasize the creation of two distinct folders.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ගමනාන්තයේ ෆෝල්ඩර දෙකක් සාදාගත/ඇතිවේ (Gamanantaye folder dekak sadagath/atheve)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The term "odredishtu" is not the standard or most natural way to express "destination" in this context. It sounds somewhat technical and less user-friendly. A more common and understandable term would be "на одредишту" or "у циљној директорији".
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: У циљној директорији ће бити два различита фолдера

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Serbian translation uses the Cyrillic alphabet. Consistency with the rest of the application/content is needed to ensure proper rendering and user experience.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Ensure all Serbian content is consistently using either Cyrillic or Latin script.
